        <h3> Basti&rsquo;s last dive </h3>
        <p> This morning the alarm clock went again so that I couldn't sleep my last dive. In the diving shop I wanted to drift comfortably along the reef edge and really enjoy the underwater world. My two companions (an older German-Asian couple) were not yet there and so I was made possible. In the conversation, it turned out that the two of them already have some experience, but have not been diving for a long time. </p>
        <p> So we only drove the boat with the boat until the reef edge could be seen from above. We jumped in and within seconds it became clear that the other two have no idea about tariff (floating state).  At first they did not come down and then clapped completely on the floor. Luckily, we were still over sand. If we had already been on the reef, a lot would have been destroyed. We then went to the edge with our guide, where the reef immediately started. This was about 8 - 11 meters of water. </p>
    </div>
