    <div class="col-md-12">
        <p> The water was so clear that from here you could still see the sandy background at about 25 meters. I stayed at a maximum of 11 meters of water because I had the new camera with me and it can only tolerate a maximum depth 15 meters. </p>
        <p> It didn't take very long before I would like to hit my two diving partners on my fingers. When you learn to dive, you are always pointed out to touch or touch anything. Corals grow extremely slowly. It takes many decades, if not for centuries until there is such a beautiful and undamaged reef as this in which we were in. Nevertheless, the two kept sticking to the corals. Aaaaaaaaaahhhh. HANDS OFF!!! I would have liked to scream. Unfortunately, nothing brings anything under water. Then I decided not to pay so much attention to the other two and not let the dive spoil. I preferred to look at the many different types of clown fishing that were sitting in their anemons and this and their family defended as soon as I came too close with my camera. In this case, the females always stood protectively in front of the Anemone and the rest of the family. Quasi according to the motto: only about my body. </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 overflow-h margin-top-20">
        <div class="box-shadow shadow-effect-3">
            <img class="img-responsive img-center img-bordered" src="{{ site.url }}/assets/img/blog/2018-philippines/small/P4050906.jpg" alt="Even more nemos.">
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <p> Shortly before we swam away from the reef edge again, towards the flatter water, I saw a beautiful red -fire fish that hovered in front of a few corals and tried to act like a plant. Even it took me a few moments to recognize where at the top, at the back and front and front of the fish. A really very nice animal. </p>
        <p> We then continue to swam into the security area to 3-5 meters. There we made the usual security stop of 3 minutes. The German Mittsaucher dropped back and once again held on to corals. It was still about 7 meters deep, i.e. a little below the security area. After my computer on the wrist said that my safety break was around, I looked around and saw that the diver was gone. I looked up and he was already on the surface. Irresponsible!!! The security stop is there to slowly breathe off the nitrogen absorbed at depth, otherwise life -threatening embolism can occur. That's why you should only appear very slowly. He completely disregarded both. As soon as we were on board, I also took him to the chest and asked him if he realized that these rules do not exist without reason. He only answers that he cannot cope with such flat water. He needs at least 15 meters to be able to dive well. Aaaaaaaaaahhh. The license should be withdrawn from such people. I was glad that the young lady could dive much better yesterday, with only 5 dives. Maybe you can go diving together in Hamburg. </p>
    </div>
